title: Norway Households' Disposable Income
description: Disposable Personal Income in Norway decreased to 367073 NOK Million in the second quarter of 2022 from 371992 NOK Million in the first quarter of 2022. Disposable Personal Income in Norway averaged 296058.04 NOK Million from 2002 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 373222 NOK Million in the fourth quarter of 2021 and a record low of 211458 NOK Million in the first quarter of 2002. In Norway, disposable income of households is the difference between compensation of employees, mixed income, property income received, social benefits and other incomes on the one side, and current taxes, property income paid and other expenditures on the other side. This page provides - Norway Disposable Personal Income - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Statistics Norway
